Akure – Kaduna State Governor, Mallam Nasir El-Rufai is to honour the first executive governor of Ondo State, the Late Pa Michael Adekunle Ajasin by delivering the 2019 Ajasin Foundation Colloquium. The event coming up on Thursday, November 28 at the International Event Center(Dome) in Akure, the Ondo State capital, was initiated in 1999 in honour of the late sage. Speaking on the event at the weekend on behalf of the Chairman, Board of Trustees(BoT), Mrs. Jumoke Anifowose, the non-executive Secretary of the foundation revealed that activities on the programme kicked off few weeks ago with the secondary schools debate competition and would be rounded off on November 27. She said: “On November 26, there will be the annual presentation to Ajasin Scholars at Owo High School, Owo initiated by Dr. ‘Bode Ogunleye,  an old student of Owo High School who is currently based in the United States of America. “The scholarship programme was instituted as his contribution in support of academic excellence in his alma mater. It involves the award of financial reward for the overall best student in each year from JS 1 – SS 3. “The best overall SS3 student will receive N100,000 per academic year through the duration of his/her University study for six years. The best student in each stream from JS 1 – SS 3 also receive N5,000 each.  The awardees in addition will receive certificates and pins to mark their academic achievement”. Meanwhile, Mrs. Anifowose, daughter of the late sage, disclosed that the final of the debate competition comes up on November 29 among some selected secondary school students at the Oyemekun Secondary School Hall in Akure.